desc: Gets the name of this command sender (usually username, but possibly "Rcon")

name: onCollideWithPlayer
desc: Called by a player entity when they collide with an entity

name: isOffsetPositionInLiquid
desc: Checks if the offset position from the entity's current position is inside of liquid. Args: x, y, z

name: setAngles
desc: Adds par1*0.15 to the entity's yaw, and *subtracts* par2*0.15 from the pitch. Clamps pitch from -90 to 90. Both arguments in degrees.

name: setCurrentItemOrArmor
desc: Sets the held item, or an armor slot. Slot 0 is held item. Slot 1-4 is armor. Params: Item, slot

name: writeMountToNBT
desc: Like writeToNBTOptional but does not check if the entity is ridden. Used for saving ridden entities with their riders.

name: interactFirst
desc: First layer of player interaction

name: setSprinting
desc: Set sprinting switch for Entity.

name: getFormattedCommandSenderName
desc: Get the formatted ChatComponent that will be used for the sender's username in chat

name: moveEntity
desc: Tries to moves the entity by the passed in displacement. Args: x, y, z

name: getBrightness
desc: Gets how bright this entity is.

name: writeToNBTOptional
desc: Either write this entity to the NBT tag given and return true, or return false without doing anything. If this returns false the entity is not saved on disk. Ridden entities return false here as they are saved with their rider.

name: isInvisibleToPlayer
desc: Only used by renderer in EntityLivingBase subclasses.\nDetermines if an entity is visible or not to a specfic player, if the entity is normally invisible.\nFor EntityLivingBase subclasses, returning false when invisible will render the entity semitransparent.

name: getDistanceSq
desc: Gets the squared distance to the position. Args: x, y, z

name: setRotationYawHead
desc: Sets the head's yaw rotation of the entity.

name: setFire
desc: Sets entity to burn for x amount of seconds, cannot lower amount of existing fire.

name: writeToNBT
desc: Save the entity to NBT (calls an abstract helper method to write extra data)

name: getDistanceToEntity
desc: Returns the distance to the entity. Args: entity

name: getDistance
desc: Gets the distance to the position. Args: x, y, z

name: dealFireDamage
desc: Will deal the specified amount of damage to the entity if the entity isn't immune to fire damage. Args: amountDamage

name: readFromNBT
desc: Reads the entity from NBT (calls an abstract helper method to read specialized data)

name: getDistanceSqToEntity
desc: Returns the squared distance to the entity. Args: entity

name: addVelocity
desc: Adds to the current velocity of the entity. Args: x, y, z

name: getFlag
desc: Returns true if the flag is active for the entity. Known flags: 0) is burning; 1) is sneaking; 2) is riding something; 3) is sprinting; 4) is eating

name: applyEntityCollision
desc: Applies a velocity to each of the entities pushing them away from each other. Args: entity

name: canTriggerWalking
desc: returns if this entity triggers Block.onEntityWalking on the blocks they walk on. used for spiders and wolves to prevent them from trampling crops

name: onUpdate
desc: Called to update the entity's position/logic.

name: getCollisionBox
desc: Returns a boundingBox used to collide the entity with other entities and blocks. This enables the entity to be pushable on contact, like boats or minecarts.

name: setVelocity
desc: Sets the velocity to the args. Args: x, y, z

name: isEntityEqual
desc: Returns true if Entity argument is equal to this Entity

name: hitByEntity
desc: Called when a player attacks an entity. If this returns true the attack will not happen.

name: copyLocationAndAnglesFrom
desc: Sets this entity's location and angles to the location and angles of the passed in entity.

name: destroyBlocksInAABB
desc: Destroys all blocks that aren't associated with 'The End' inside the given bounding box.

name: collideWithEntities
desc: Pushes all entities inside the list away from the enderdragon.

name: simplifyAngle
desc: Simplifies the value of a number by adding/subtracting 180 to the point that the number is between -180 and 180.

name: getMovementOffsets
desc: Returns a double[3] array with movement offsets, used to calculate trailing tail/neck positions. [0] = yaw offset, [1] = y offset, [2] = unused, always 0. Parameters: buffer index offset, partial ticks.

name: createEnderPortal
desc: Creates the ender portal leading back to the normal world after defeating the enderdragon.

name: attackEntitiesInList
desc: Attacks all entities inside this list, dealing 5 hearts of damage.

name: updateDragonEnderCrystal
desc: Updates the state of the enderdragon's current endercrystal.

name: setNewTarget
desc: Sets a new target for the flight AI. It can be a random coordinate or a nearby player.

name: attackDragonFrom
desc: Provides a way to cause damage to an ender dragon.

name: launchWitherSkullToCoords
desc: Launches a Wither skull toward (par2, par4, par6)

name: updateWatchedTargetId
desc: Updates the target entity ID

name: ignite
desc: Initializes this Wither's explosion sequence and makes it invulnerable. Called immediately after spawning.

name: isArmored
desc: Returns whether the wither is armored with its boss armor or not by checking whether its health is below half of its maximum.

name: getWatchedTargetId
desc: Returns the target entity ID if present, or -1 if not @param par1 The target offset, should be from 0-2

name: setThrowableHeading
desc: Similar to setArrowHeading, it's point the throwable entity to a x, y, z direction.

name: setDamageTaken
desc: Sets the damage taken from the last hit.

name: setTimeSinceHit
desc: Sets the time to count down from since the last time entity was hit.

name: setIsBoatEmpty
desc: true if no player in boat

name: setForwardDirection
desc: Sets the forward direction of the entity.

name: getDamageTaken
desc: Gets the damage taken from the last hit.

name: getTimeSinceHit
desc: Gets the time since the last hit.

name: getForwardDirection
desc: Gets the forward direction of the entity.

name: moveTowards
desc: The location the eye should float/move towards. Currently used for moving towards the nearest stronghold. Args: strongholdX, strongholdY, strongholdZ

name: explodeCart
desc: Makes the minecart explode.

name: ignite
desc: Ignites this TNT cart.

name: getFuseTicks
desc: Gets the remaining fuse time in ticks.

name: isIgnited
desc: Returns true if the TNT minecart is ignited.

name: setEntityItemStack
desc: Sets the ItemStack for this entity

name: combineItems
desc: Tries to merge this item with the item passed as the parameter. Returns true if successful. Either this item or the other item will  be removed from the world.

name: setAgeToCreativeDespawnTime
desc: sets the age of the item so that it'll despawn one minute after it has been dropped (instead of five). Used when items are dropped from players in creative mode

name: getEntityItem
desc: Returns the ItemStack corresponding to the Entity (Note: if no item exists, will log an error but still return an ItemStack containing Block.stone)

name: searchForOtherItemsNearby
desc: Looks for other itemstacks nearby and tries to stack them together

name: removeFrameFromMap
desc: Removes the dot representing this frame's position from the map when the item frame is broken.

name: getRotation
desc: Return the rotation of the item currently on this frame.

name: getXPSplit
desc: Get a fragment of the maximum experience points value for the supplied value of experience points value.

name: getXpValue
desc: Returns the XP value of this XP orb.

name: getTextureByXP
desc: Returns a number from 1 to 10 based on how much XP this orb is worth. This is used by RenderXPOrb to determine what texture to use.

name: canTransfer
desc: Returns whether the hopper cart can currently transfer an item.

name: setBlocked
desc: Set whether this hopper minecart is being blocked by an activator rail.

name: setTransferTicker
desc: Sets the transfer ticker, used to determine the delay between transfers.

name: getBlocked
desc: Get whether this hopper minecart is being blocked by an activator rail.

name: getPosOffset
desc: This method is used to determine the minecart's render orientation, by computing a position along the rail slightly before and slightly after the minecart's actual position.

name: setDamage
desc: Sets the current amount of damage the minecart has taken. Decreases over time. The cart breaks when this is over 40.

name: onActivatorRailPass
desc: Called every tick the minecart is on an activator rail. Args: x, y, z, is the rail receiving power

name: createMinecart
desc: Creates a new minecart of the specified type in the specified location in the given world. par0World - world to create the minecart in, double par1,par3,par5 represent x,y,z respectively. int par7 specifies the type: 1 for MinecartChest, 2 for MinecartFurnace, 3 for MinecartTNT, 4 for MinecartMobSpawner, 5 for MinecartHopper and 0 for a standard empty minecart

name: setMinecartName
desc: Sets the minecart's name.

name: setRollingAmplitude
desc: Sets the rolling amplitude the cart rolls while being attacked.

name: getDamage
desc: Gets the current amount of damage the minecart has taken. Decreases over time. The cart breaks when this is over 40.

name: setRollingDirection
desc: Sets the rolling direction the cart rolls while being attacked. Can be 1 or -1.

name: getRollingAmplitude
desc: Gets the rolling amplitude the cart rolls while being attacked.

name: hasCustomInventoryName
desc: Returns if the inventory is named

name: getRollingDirection
desc: Gets the rolling direction the cart rolls while being attacked. Can be 1 or -1.

name: getCustomNameTag
desc: Gets the custom name assigned to this entity. If no custom name has been assigned, returns an empty string.

name: getTntPlacedBy
desc: returns null or the entityliving it was placed or ignited by

name: attackEntityWithRangedAttack
desc: Attack the specified entity using a ranged attack.

name: readAttributeModifierFromNBT
desc: Creates an AttributeModifier from an NBTTagCompound

name: writeAttributeInstanceToNBT
desc: Creates an NBTTagCompound from an AttributeInstance, including its AttributeModifiers

name: writeAttributeModifierToNBT
desc: Creates an NBTTagCompound from an AttributeModifier

name: writeBaseAttributeMapToNBT
desc: Creates an NBTTagList from a BaseAttributeMap, including all its AttributeInstances

name: sendPacketToTrackedPlayers
desc: Send the given packet to all players tracking this entity.

name: sendLocationToAllClients
desc: also sends velocity, rotation, and riding info.

name: sendMetadataToAllAssociatedPlayers
desc: Sends the entity metadata (DataWatcher) and attributes to all players tracking this entity, including the entity itself if a player.

name: tryStartWachingThis
desc: if the player is more than the distance threshold (typically 64) then the player is removed instead

name: createSpawnPacket
desc: Creates a spawn packet for the entity managed by this entry.

name: removePlayerFromTracker
desc: Remove a tracked player from our list and tell the tracked player to destroy us from their world.

name: getPeacefulCreature
desc: Gets whether or not this creature type is peaceful.

name: getAnimal
desc: Return whether this creature type is an animal.

name: hasChanges
desc: true if one or more object was changed

name: getWatchableObjectByte
desc: gets the bytevalue of a watchable object

name: addObjectByDataType
desc: Add a new object for the DataWatcher to watch, using the specified data type.

name: addObject
desc: adds a new object to dataWatcher to watch, to update an already existing object see updateObject. Arguments: data Value Id, Object to add

name: writeWatchableObjectToPacketBuffer
desc: Writes a watchable object (entity attribute of type {byte, short, int, float, string, ItemStack, ChunkCoordinates}) to the specified PacketBuffer

name: writeWatchedListToPacketBuffer
desc: Writes the list of watched objects (entity attribute of type {byte, short, int, float, string, ItemStack, ChunkCoordinates}) to the specified PacketBuffer

name: updateObject
desc: updates an already existing object

name: readWatchedListFromPacketBuffer
desc: Reads a list of watched objects (entity attribute of type {byte, short, int, float, string, ItemStack, ChunkCoordinates}) from the supplied PacketBuffer

name: getWatchableObjectInt
desc: gets a watchable object and returns it as a Integer

name: getWatchableObjectString
desc: gets a watchable object and returns it as a String

name: getWatchableObjectItemStack
desc: Get a watchable object as an ItemStack.

name: getWatchedObject
desc: is threadsafe, unless it throws an exception, then

name: setBesideClimbableBlock
desc: Updates the WatchableObject (Byte) created in entityInit(), setting it to 0x01 if par1 is true or 0x00 if it is false.

name: isBesideClimbableBlock
desc: Returns true if the WatchableObject (Byte) is 0x01 otherwise returns false. The WatchableObject is updated using setBesideClimableBlock.

name: getCreeperFlashIntensity
desc: Params: (Float)Render tick. Returns the intensity of the creeper's flash when it is ignited.

name: setCreeperState
desc: Sets the state of creeper, -1 to idle and 1 to be 'in fuse'

name: getPowered
desc: Returns true if the creeper is powered by a lightning bolt.

name: getCreeperState
desc: Returns the current state of creeper, -1 is idle, 1 is 'in fuse'

name: explode
desc: Creates an explosion as determined by this creeper's power and explosion radius.

name: isValidLightLevel
desc: Checks to make sure the light is not too bright where the mob is spawning

name: setSkeletonType
desc: Set this skeleton's type.

name: setCombatTask
desc: sets this entity's combat AI.

name: getSkeletonType
desc: Return this skeleton's type.

name: setAggressive
desc: Set whether this witch is aggressive at an entity.

name: getAggressive
desc: Return whether this witch is aggressive at an entity.

name: getSlimeParticle
desc: Returns the name of a particle effect that may be randomly created by EntitySlime.onUpdate()

name: getJumpDelay
desc: Gets the amount of time the slime needs to wait between jumps.

name: canDamagePlayer
desc: Indicates weather the slime is able to damage the player (based upon the slime's size)

name: getAttackStrength
desc: Gets the amount of damage dealt to the player when ""attacked"" by the slime.

name: getJumpSound
desc: Returns the name of the sound played when the slime jumps.

name: makesSoundOnLand
desc: Returns true if the slime makes a sound when it lands after a jump (based upon the slime's size)

name: getSlimeSize
desc: Returns the size of the slime.

name: makesSoundOnJump
desc: Returns true if the slime makes a sound when it jumps (based upon the slime's size)

name: isCourseTraversable
desc: True if the ghast has an unobstructed line of travel to the waypoint.

name: multiplySize
desc: Multiplies the height and width by the provided float.

name: startConversion
desc: Starts converting this zombie into a villager. The zombie converts into a villager after the specified time in ticks.

name: setBreakDoorsAItask
desc: Sets or removes EntityAIBreakDoor task

name: isVillager
desc: Return whether this zombie is a villager.

name: isConverting
desc: Returns whether this zombie is in the process of converting to a villager

name: convertToVillager
desc: Convert this zombie into a villager.

name: getConversionTimeBoost
desc: Return the amount of time decremented from conversionTime every tick.

name: setChild
desc: Set whether this zombie is a child.

name: setVillager
desc: Set whether this zombie is a villager.

name: setChildSize
desc: sets the size of the entity to be half of its current size if true.

name: becomeAngryAt
desc: Causes this PigZombie to become angry at the supplied Entity (which will be a player).

name: setCarryingData
desc: Set the metadata of the block an enderman carries

name: setCarriedBlock
desc: Sets the block carried by this Enderman

name: teleportRandomly
desc: Teleport the enderman to a random nearby position

name: teleportToEntity
desc: Teleport the enderman to another entity

name: getCarriedBlock
desc: Gets the block carried by this Enderman

name: getCarryingData
desc: Get the metadata of the block an enderman carries

name: shouldAttackPlayer
desc: Checks to see if this enderman should be attacking this player

name: teleportTo
desc: Teleport the enderman

name: requestTexturePackLoad
desc: on receiving this message the client (if permission is given) will download the requested textures

name: handleFalling
desc: process player falling based on movement packet

name: getNextWindowId
desc: get the next window id to use

name: removeEntity
desc: Sends a packet to the player to remove an entity.

name: updateBiomesExplored
desc: Updates all biomes that have been explored by this player and triggers Adventuring Time if player qualifies.

name: updateHeldItem
desc: updates item held by mouse

name: closeContainer
desc: Closes the container the player currently has open.

name: setPlayerHealthUpdated
desc: this function is called when a players inventory is sent to him, lastHealth is updated on any dimension transitions, then reset.

name: getPlayerIP
desc: Gets the player's IP address. Used in /banip.

name: getStatFile
desc: Gets the stats file for reading achievements

name: damageArmor
desc: Damages armor in each slot by the specified amount.

name: consumeInventoryItem
desc: removed one item of specified Item from inventory (if it is in a stack, the stack size will reduce with 1)

name: clearInventory
desc: Clear this player's inventory (including armor), using the specified Item and metadata as filters or -1 for no filter.

name: addItemStackToInventory
desc: Adds the item stack to the inventory, returns false if it is impossible.

name: writeToNBT
desc: Writes the inventory out as a list of compound tags. This is where the slot indices are used (+100 for armor, +80 for crafting).

name: hasItem
desc: Checks if a specified Item is inside the inventory

name: setItemStack
desc: Set the stack helds by mouse, used in GUI/Container

name: readFromNBT
desc: Reads from the given tag list and fills the slots in the inventory with the correct items.

name: copyInventory
desc: Copy the ItemStack contents from another InventoryPlayer instance

name: changeCurrentItem
desc: Switch the current item to the next one or the previous one

name: hasItemStack
desc: Returns true if the specified ItemStack exists in the inventory.

name: armorItemInSlot
desc: returns a player armor item (as itemstack) contained in specified armor slot.

name: storeItemStack
desc: stores an itemstack in the users inventory

name: storePartialItemStack
desc: This function stores as many items of an ItemStack as possible in a matching slot and returns the quantity of left over items.

name: getCurrentItem
desc: Returns the item stack currently held by the player.

name: getHotbarSize
desc: Get the size of the player hotbar inventory

name: getFirstEmptyStack
desc: Returns the first item stack that is empty.

name: decrementAnimations
desc: Decrement the number of animations remaining. Only called on client side. This is used to handle the animation of receiving a block.

name: getTotalArmorValue
desc: Based on the damage values and maximum damage values of each armor item, returns the current armor value.

name: dropAllItems
desc: Drop all armor and main inventory items.

name: getItemStack
desc: Stack helds by mouse, used in GUI and Containers

name: addExhaustion
desc: increases exhaustion level by supplied amount

name: addExperienceLevel
desc: Add experience levels to this player.

name: sleepInBedAt
desc: puts player to sleep on specified bed if possible

name: setItemInUse
desc: sets the itemInUse when the use item button is clicked. Args: itemstack, int maxItemUseDuration

name: dropPlayerItemWithRandomChoice
desc: Args: itemstack, flag

name: dropItem
verifyRespawnCoordinates
desc: Ensure that a block enabling respawning exists at the specified coordinates and find an empty space nearby to spawn.

name: setGameType
desc: Sets the player's game mode and sends it to them.

name: canHarvestBlock
desc: Checks if the player has the ability to harvest a block (checks current inventory item for a tool if necessary)

name: getCurrentPlayerStrVsBlock
desc: Returns how strong the player is against the specified block at this moment

name: displayGUIEditSign
desc: Displays the GUI for editing a sign. Args: tileEntitySign

name: getUUID
desc: Gets a players UUID given their GameProfie

name: triggerAchievement
desc: Will trigger the specified trigger.

name: addStat
desc: Adds a value to a statistic field.

name: setSpawnChunk
desc: Defines a spawn coordinate to player spawn. Used by bed after the player sleep on it.

name: displayGUIChest
desc: Displays the GUI for interacting with a chest inventory. Args: chestInventory

name: joinEntityItemWithWorld
desc: Joins the passed in entity item with the world. Args: entityItem

name: clonePlayer
desc: Copies the values from the given player into this player if boolean par2 is true. Always clones Ender Chest Inventory.

name: dropOneItem
desc: Called when player presses the drop item key

name: wakeUpPlayer
desc: Wake up the player if they're sleeping.

name: displayGUIWorkbench
desc: Displays the crafting GUI for a workbench.

name: displayGUIBook
desc: Displays the GUI for interacting with a book.

name: onCriticalHit
desc: Called when the player performs a critical hit on the Entity. Args: entity that was hit critically

name: getArmorVisibility
desc: When searching for vulnerable players, if a player is invisible, the return value of this is the chance of seeing them anyway.

name: getCurrentEquippedItem
desc: Returns the currently being used item by the player.

name: destroyCurrentEquippedItem
desc: Destroys the currently equipped item from the player's inventory.

name: getGameProfile
desc: Returns the GameProfile for this player

name: getBedOrientationInDegrees
desc: Returns the orientation of the bed in degrees.

name: isPlayerFullyAsleep
desc: Returns whether or not the player is asleep and the screen has fully faded.

name: getBedLocation
desc: Returns the location of the bed the player will respawn at, or null if the player has not slept in a bed.

name: xpBarCap
desc: This method returns the cap amount of experience that the experience bar can hold. With each level, the experience cap on the player's experience bar is raised by 10.

name: getFoodStats
desc: Returns the player's FoodStats object.

name: shouldHeal
desc: Checks if the player's health is not full and not zero.

name: getInventoryEnderChest
desc: Returns the InventoryEnderChest of this player.

name: getItemInUse
desc: returns the ItemStack containing the itemInUse

name: getItemInUseCount
desc: Returns the item in use count

name: isUsingItem
desc: Checks if the entity is currently using an item (e.g., bow, food, sword) by holding down the useItemButton

name: getItemInUseDuration
desc: gets the duration for how long the current itemInUse has been in use

name: setScore
desc: Set player's score

name: displayGUIAnvil
desc: Displays the GUI for interacting with an anvil.

name: updateItemUse
desc: Plays sounds and makes particles for item in use state

name: isCurrentToolAdventureModeExempt
desc: Returns true if the given block can be mined with the current tool in adventure mode.

name: resetHeight
desc: sets the players height back to normal after doing things like sleeping and dieing

name: isInBed
desc: Checks if the player is currently in a bed

name: closeScreen
desc: sets current screen to null (used on escape buttons of GUIs); sets current crafting inventory back to the 2x2 square

name: addMovementStat
desc: Adds a value to a movement statistic field - like run, walk, swin or climb.

name: addMountedMovementStat
desc: Adds a value to a mounted movement statistic field - by minecart, boat, or pig.

name: onItemUseFinish
desc: Used for when item use count runs out, ie: eating completed

name: sendPlayerAbilities
desc: Sends the player's abilities to the server (if there is one).

name: attackTargetEntityWithCurrentItem
desc: Attacks for the player the targeted entity with the currently equipped item.  The equipped item has hitEntity called on it. Args: targetEntity

name: addScore
desc: Add to player's score

name: addExperience
desc: Add experience points to player.

name: onImpact
desc: Called when this EntityFireball hits a block or entity.

name: getMotionFactor
desc: Return the motion factor for this projectile. The factor is multiplied by the original motion.

name: onImpact
desc: Called when this EntityThrowable hits a block or entity.

name: getGravityVelocity
desc: Gets the amount of gravity to apply to the thrown entity with each tick.

name: setInvulnerable
desc: Set whether this skull comes from an invulnerable (aura) wither boss.

name: isInvulnerable
desc: Return whether this skull comes from an invulnerable (aura) wither boss.

name: setKnockbackStrength
desc: Sets the amount of knockback the arrow applies when it hits a mob.

name: setIsCritical
desc: Whether the arrow has a stream of critical hit particles flying behind it.

name: getIsCritical
desc: Whether the arrow has a stream of critical hit particles flying behind it.

name: setPotionDamage
desc: Sets the PotionEffect by the given id of the potion effect.

name: getPotionDamage
desc: Returns the damage value of the thrown potion that this EntityPotion represents.

name: getArmorItemForSlot
desc: Params: Armor slot, Item tier

name: canAttackClass
desc: Returns true if this entity can attack entities of the specified class.

name: faceEntity
desc: Changes pitch and yaw so that the entity calling the function is facing the entity provided as an argument.

name: interact
desc: Called when a player interacts with a mob. e.g. gets milk from a cow, gets into the saddle on a pig.

name: clearLeashed
desc: Removes the leash from this entity. Second parameter tells whether to send a packet to surrounding players.

name: updateRotation
desc: Arguments: current rotation, intended rotation, max increment.

name: setLeashedToEntity
getMaxSpawnedInChunk
desc: Will return how many at most can spawn in a chunk at once.

name: addRandomArmor
desc: Makes entity wear random armor based on difficulty

name: enchantEquipment
desc: Enchants the entity's armor and held item based on difficulty

name: canBeSteered
desc: returns true if all the conditions for steering the entity are met. For pigs, this is true if it is being ridden by a player and the player is holding a carrot-on-a-stick

name: enablePersistence
desc: Enable the Entity persistence

name: isNoDespawnRequired
desc: Return the persistenceRequired field (whether this entity is allowed to naturally despawn)

name: updateLeashedState
desc: Applies logic related to leashes, for example dragging the entity or breaking the leash.

name: getCanSpawnHere
desc: Checks if the entity's current position is a valid location to spawn this entity.

name: getRenderSizeModifier
desc: Returns render size modifier

name: setAttackTarget
desc: Sets the active target the Task system uses for tracking

name: setAlwaysRenderNameTag
desc: Set whether this Entity's AI is disabled

name: getEntitySenses
desc: returns the EntitySenses Object for the EntityLiving

name: getAttackTarget
desc: Gets the active target the Task system uses for tracking

name: eatGrassBonus
desc: This function applies the benefits of growing back wool and faster growing up to the acting entity. (This function is used in the AIEatGrass)

name: getTalkInterval
desc: Get number of ticks, at least during which the living entity will be silent.

name: playLivingSound
desc: Plays living's sound at its position

name: spawnExplosionParticle
desc: Spawns an explosion particle around the Entity's location

name: getLivingSound
desc: Returns the sound this mob makes while it's alive.

name: canDespawn
desc: Determines if an entity can be despawned, used on idle far away entities

name: despawnEntity
desc: Makes the entity despawn if requirements are reached

name: getVerticalFaceSpeed
desc: The speed it takes to move the entityliving's rotationPitch through the faceEntity method. This is only currently use in wolves.

name: addGrowth
desc: "Adds the value of the parameter times 20 to the age of this entity. If the entity is an adult (if the entity's age is greater than 0), it will have no effect."

name: setScaleForAge
desc: "Sets the scale for an ageable entity according to the boolean parameter, which says if it's a child."

name: setGrowingAge
desc: The age value may be negative or positive or zero. If it's negative, it get's incremented on each tick, if it's positive, it get's decremented each tick. With a negative value the Entity is considered a child.

name: getGrowingAge
desc: The age value may be negative or positive or zero. If it's negative, it get's incremented on each tick, if it's positive, it get's decremented each tick. Don't confuse this with EntityLiving.getAge. With a negative value the Entity is considered a child.

name: setSaved
desc: @see #isSaved

name: isSaved
desc: @see #isSaved

name: registerAttribute
desc: Registers an attribute with this AttributeMap, returns a modifiable AttributeInstance associated with this map

name: getAttribute
desc: Get the Attribute this is an instance of

name: getModifier
desc: Returns attribute modifier, if any, by the given UUID

name: isStairOrSlab
desc: True if the block is a stair block or a slab block

name: isSpeedBoosted
desc: Return whether the entity's speed is boosted.

name: boostSpeed
desc: Boost the entity's movement speed.

name: isControlledByPlayer

desc: Returns whether the EntityAIBase should begin execution.

name: startExecuting

name: resetTask
desc: Resets the task

name: updateTask
desc: Updates the task

name: isInterruptible
desc: Determine if this AI Task is interruptible by a higher (= lower value) priority task.

name: getMutexBits
desc: Get a bitmask telling which other tasks may not run concurrently. The test is a simple bitwise AND - if it yields zero, the two tasks may run concurrently, if not - they must run exclusively from each other.

name: setSitting

name: setCollarColor

name: isEntityUndead

Returns : 1 = clear, 0 = blocked, -1 = water (if avoiding water), -2 = lava (if not already in lava), -3 = fence or rails, -4 = closed trapdoor, 2 = open trapdoor or water (if not avoiding) or open door (if can pass trhough). Args : entity, posX, posY, posZ, entitySize, avoidsWater, canPassClosedWoodenDoor, scanPassOpe

name: isLiquid

name: setBurning

desc: Returns if the block can burn or not.

desc: Actualise metadata (orientation) value from neighbors blocks (another chest ? Opaque block ?)

name: getBlockBoundsMaxY
desc: returns the block bounderies maxY value

name: getBlockBoundsMinZ
desc: returns the block bounderies minZ value

name: getBlockBoundsMaxZ
desc: returns the block bounderies maxZ value

desc: Returns the CreativeTab to display the given block on.

name: setCreativeTab

Sets this block's creative inventory tab.

NOTE: this method should only be used during the block's creation before it is registered.

Performs a block event. Block events are queued on the server, and executed once per
tick. Successful block events are synced with clients that are within range. Block events
are most notably used by pistons to handle extension and retraction, but note blocks
also use them to play sounds.

@return whether the block event was successful.

bit property

desc: Writes a (UTF-8 encoded) String to this buffer. Will throw IOException if String length exceeds 32767 bytes

name: readNBTTagCompoundFromBuffer
desc: Reads a compressed NBTTagCompound from this buffer

name: writeVarIntToBuffer
desc: Writes a compressed int to the buffer. The smallest number of bytes to fit the passed int will be written. Of each such byte only 7 bits will be used to describe the actual value since its most significant bit dictates whether the next byte is part of that same int. Micro-optimization for int values that are expected to have values below 128.

name: readItemStackFromBuffer
desc: Reads an ItemStack from this buffer

name: readStringFromBuffer
desc: Reads a string from this buffer. Expected parameter is maximum allowed string length. Will throw IOException if string length exceeds this value!

name: processAnimation
desc: Processes the player swinging its held item

name: processTabComplete
desc: Retrieves possible tab completions for the requested command string and sends them to the client

name: processChatMessage
desc: Process chat messages (broadcast back to clients) and commands (executes)

name: processClientStatus
desc: Processes the client status updates: respawn attempt from player, opening statistics or achievements, or acquiring 'open inventory' achievement

name: processClientSettings
desc: Updates serverside copy of client settings: language, render distance, chat visibility, chat colours, difficulty, and whether to show the cape

name: processConfirmTransaction
desc: Received in response to the server requesting to confirm that the client-side open container matches the servers' after a mismatched container-slot manipulation. It will unlock the player's ability to manipulate the container contents

name: processEnchantItem
desc: Enchants the item identified by the packet given some convoluted conditions (matching window, which should/shouldn't be in use?)

name: processClickWindow
desc: Executes a container/inventory slot manipulation as indicated by the packet. Sends the serverside result if they didn't match the indicated result and prevents further manipulation by the player until he confirms that it has the same open container/inventory

name: processCloseWindow
desc: Processes the client closing windows (container)

name: processVanilla250Packet
desc: Synchronizes serverside and clientside book contents and signing

name: processUseEntity
desc: Processes interactions ((un)leashing, opening command block GUI) and attacks on an entity with players currently equipped item

name: processKeepAlive
desc: Updates a players' ping statistics

name: processPlayer
desc: Processes clients perspective on player positioning and/or orientation

name: processPlayerAbilities
desc: Processes a player starting/stopping flying

name: processPlayerDigging
desc: Processes the player initiating/stopping digging on a particular spot, as well as a player dropping items?. (0: initiated, 1: reinitiated, 2? , 3-4 drop item (respectively without or with player control), 5: stopped; x,y,z, side clicked on;)

name: processEntityAction
desc: Processes a range of action-types: sneaking, sprinting, waking from sleep, opening the inventory or setting jump height of the horse the player is riding

name: processInput
desc: Processes player movement input. Includes walking, strafing, jumping, sneaking; excludes riding and toggling flying/sprinting

name: processHeldItemChange
desc: Updates which quickbar slot is selected

name: processCreativeInventoryAction
desc: Update the server with an ItemStack in a slot.

name: processPlayerBlockPlacement
desc: Processes block placement and block activation (anvil, furnace, etc.)

name: getXCoordinate

name: getYCoordinate
desc: Gets the y coordinate to spawn the particle.

name: getZCoordinate
desc: Gets the z coordinate to spawn the particle.

name: getXOffset
desc: Gets the x coordinate offset for the particle. The particle may use the offset for particle spread.

name: getYOffset
desc: Gets the y coordinate offset for the particle. The particle may use the offset for particle spread.

name: getZOffset
desc: Gets the z coordinate offset for the particle. The particle may use the offset for particle spread.

name: getParticleSpeed
desc: Gets the speed of the particle animation (used in client side rendering).

name: getParticleCount
desc: Gets the amount of particles to spawn

name: isChat
desc: This method returns true if the type is SYSTEM or ABOVE_HOTBAR, and false if CHAT

name: getData1
desc: instrument data for noteblocks

name: getData2
desc: pitch data for noteblocks

name: getPlacedBlockOffsetX
desc: Returns the offset from xPosition where the actual click took place.

name: getPlacedBlockOffsetY
desc: Returns the offset from yPosition where the actual click took place.

name: getPlacedBlockOffsetZ
desc: Returns the offset from zPosition where the actual click took place.

name: getDiggedBlockX
desc: Returns X coordinate of the block that was digged.

name: getDiggedBlockY
desc: Returns Y coordinate of the block that was digged.

name: getDiggedBlockZ
desc: Returns Z coordinate of the block that was digged.

name: getDiggedBlockStatus
desc: Status of the digging (started, ongoing, broken).

name: handlePlayerPosLook
desc: Handles changes in player positioning and rotation such as when travelling to a new dimension, (re)spawning, mounting horses etc. Seems to immediately reply to the server with the clients post-processing perspective on the player positioning

name: handleSpawnObject
desc: Spawns an instance of the objecttype indicated by the packet and sets its position and momentum

name: handleSpawnExperienceOrb
desc: Spawns an experience orb and sets its value (amount of XP)

name: handleSpawnGlobalEntity
desc: Handles globally visible entities. Used in vanilla for lightning bolts

name: handleSpawnMob
desc: Spawns the mob entity at the specified location, with the specified rotation, momentum and type. Updates the entities Datawatchers with the entity metadata specified in the packet

name: handleSpawnPainting
desc: Handles the spawning of a painting object

name: handleSpawnPlayer
desc: Handles the creation of a nearby player entity, sets the position and held item

name: handleAnimation
desc: Renders a specified animation: Waking up a player, a living entity swinging its currently held item, being hurt or receiving a critical hit by normal or magical means

name: handleStatistics
desc: Updates the players statistics or achievements

name: handleBlockBreakAnim
desc: Updates all registered IWorldAccess instances with destroyBlockInWorldPartially

name: handleUpdateTileEntity
desc: Updates the NBTTagCompound metadata of instances of the following entitytypes: Mob spawners, command blocks, beacons, skulls, flowerpot

name: handleBlockAction
desc: Triggers Block.onBlockEventReceived, which is implemented in BlockPistonBase for extension/retraction, BlockNote for setting the instrument (including audiovisual feedback) and in BlockContainer to set the number of players accessing a (Ender)Chest

name: handleBlockChange
desc: Updates the block and metadata and generates a blockupdate (and notify the clients)

name: handleTabComplete
desc: Displays the available command-completion options the server knows of

name: handleChat
desc: Prints a chatmessage in the chat GUI

name: handleMultiBlockChange
desc: Received from the servers PlayerManager if between 1 and 64 blocks in a chunk are changed. If only one block requires an update, the server sends S23PacketBlockChange and if 64 or more blocks are changed, the server sends S21PacketChunkData

name: handleConfirmTransaction
desc: Verifies that the server and client are synchronized with respect to the inventory/container opened by the player and confirms if it is the case.

name: handleCloseWindow
desc: Resets the ItemStack held in hand and closes the window that is opened

name: handleOpenWindow
desc: Displays a GUI by ID. In order starting from id 0: Chest, Workbench, Furnace, Dispenser, Enchanting table, Brewing stand, Villager merchant, Beacon, Anvil, Hopper, Dropper, Horse

name: handleWindowItems
desc: Handles the placement of a specified ItemStack in a specified container/inventory slot

name: handleWindowProperty
desc: Sets the progressbar of the opened window to the specified value

name: handleSetSlot
desc: Handles pickin up an ItemStack or dropping one in your inventory or an open (non-creative) container

name: handleCustomPayload
desc: Handles packets that have room for a channel specification. Vanilla implemented channels are "MC|TrList" to acquire a MerchantRecipeList trades for a villager merchant, "MC|Brand" which sets the server brand? on the player instance and finally "MC|RPack" which the server uses to communicate the identifier of the default server resourcepack for the client to load.

name: handleDisconnect
desc: Closes the network channel

name: handleEntityStatus
desc: Invokes the entities' handleUpdateHealth method which is implemented in LivingBase (hurt/death), MinecartMobSpawner (spawn delay), FireworkRocket & MinecartTNT (explosion), IronGolem (throwing,...), Witch (spawn particles), Zombie (villager transformation), Animal (breeding mode particles), Horse (breeding/smoke particles), Sheep (...), Tameable (...), Villager (particles for breeding mode, angry and happy), Wolf (...)

name: handleExplosion
desc: Initiates a new explosion (sound, particles, drop spawn) for the affected blocks indicated by the packet.

name: handleChunkData
desc: Updates the specified chunk with the supplied data, marks it for re-rendering and lighting recalculation

name: handleParticles
desc: Spawns a specified number of particles at the specified location with a randomized displacement according to specified bounds

name: handleJoinGame
desc: Registers some server properties (gametype,hardcore-mode,terraintype,difficulty,player limit), creates a new WorldClient and sets the player initial dimension

name: handleMaps
desc: Updates the worlds MapStorage with the specified MapData for the specified map-identifier and invokes a MapItemRenderer for it

name: handleEntityMovement
desc: Updates the specified entity's position by the specified relative moment and absolute rotation. Note that subclassing of the packet allows for the specification of a subset of this data (e.g. only rel. position, abs. rotation or both).

name: handleSignEditorOpen
desc: Creates a sign in the specified location if it didn't exist and opens the GUI to edit its text

name: handleUseBed
desc: Retrieves the player identified by the packet, puts him to sleep if possible (and flags whether all players are asleep)

name: handleDestroyEntities
desc: Locally eliminates the entities. Invoked by the server when the items are in fact destroyed, or the player is no longer registered as required to monitor them. The latter  happens when distance between the player and item increases beyond a certain treshold (typically the viewing distance)

name: handleRemoveEntityEffect
desc: Handle a remove entity effect packet.

name: handleRespawn
desc: respawns the player

name: handleEntityHeadLook
desc: Updates the direction in which the specified entity is looking, normally this head rotation is independent of the rotation of the entity itself

name: handleHeldItemChange
desc: Updates which hotbar slot of the player is currently selected

name: handleDisplayScoreboard
desc: Removes or sets the ScoreObjective to be displayed at a particular scoreboard position (list, sidebar, below name)

name: handleEntityMetadata
desc: Invoked when the server registers new proximate objects in your watchlist or when objects in your watchlist have changed -> Registers any changes locally

name: handleEntityVelocity
desc: Sets the velocity of the specified entity to the specified value

name: handleUpdateHealth
desc: Recieves player health from the server and then proceeds to set it locally on the client.

name: handleScoreboardObjective

name: handleTeams

name: handleUpdateScore
desc: Either updates the score with a specified value or removes the score for an objective

name: handleUpdateSign
desc: Updates a specified sign with the specified text lines

name: handleEntityTeleport
desc: Updates an entity's position and rotation as specified by the packet

name: handleEntityProperties
desc: Updates en entity's attributes and their respective modifiers, which are used for speed bonusses (player sprinting, animals fleeing, baby speed), weapon/tool attackDamage, hostiles followRange randomization, zombie maxHealth and knockback resistance as well as reinforcement spawning chance.

name: addLocalEndpoint
desc: Adds a channel that listens locally

name: addLanEndpoint

name: terminateEndpoints

name: networkTick

name: setPlayerLocation

name: kickPlayerFromServer

name: addTime

name: notifyOperators

name: getCustomName

name: getGameModeFromCommand

name: toggleDownfall

name: canCommandSenderUseCommand

name: addChatMessage
desc: Notifies this sender of some sort of information.  This is for messages intended to display to the user.  Used for typical output (like "you asked for whether or not this game rule is set, so here's your answer"), warnings (like "I fetched this block for you by ID, but I'd like you to know that every time you do this, I die a little inside"), and errors (like "it's not called iron_pixacke, silly").

name: getEntityWorld

desc: Return the position for this command sender.

name: canCommandSenderUseCommand
desc: Returns true if the given command sender is allowed to use this command.

getPossibleCommands

name: setAdminCommander

name: getBlockByText

name: isDifficultyScaled
desc: Return whether this damage source will have its damage amount scaled based on the current difficulty.

name: addStats

desc:
Draws either a gradient over the background world (if there is a world), or a dirt screen if there is no world.
 
This method should usually be called before doing any other rendering; otherwise weird results will occur if there is no world, and the world will not be tinted if there is.
 
Do not call after having already done other rendering, as it will draw over it.
 
@param tint Used to offset vertical position for the texture in options_background.png, if there is no world (i.e. if {@link #func_146278_c} is called). In vanilla, this is always 0.

name: updateEntity
desc: Will update the entity in the world if the chunk the entity is in is currently loaded. Args: entity

name: updateEntities
desc: Updates (and cleans up) entities and tile entities

name: getPrecipitationHeight
desc: Gets the height to which rain/snow will fall. Calculates it if not already stored.

name: joinEntityInSurroundings
desc: spwans an entity and loads surrounding chunks

name: setThunderStrength
desc: Sets the strength of the thunder.

name: getTopSolidOrLiquidBlock
desc: Finds the highest block on the x, z coordinate that is solid and returns its y coord. Args x, z

name: canBlockSeeTheSky
desc: Checks if the specified block is able to see the sky

name: createChunkProvider
desc: Creates the chunk provider for this world. Called in the constructor. Retrieves provider from worldProvider?

name: getRainStrength
desc: Not sure about this actually. Reverting this one myself.

name: getFullBlockLightValue
desc: Does the same as getBlockLightValue_do but without checking if its not a normal block

name: setRainStrength
desc: Sets the strength of the rain.

name: getBlockLightValue
desc: Gets the light value of a block location

name: markBlockForRenderUpdate
desc: On the client, re-renders this block. On the server, does nothing. Used for lighting updates.

name: getLightBrightness
desc: Returns how bright the block is shown as which is the block's light value looked up in a lookup table (light values aren't linear for brightness). Args: x, y, z

name: updateWeather
desc: Updates all weather states.

name: isBlockFreezable
desc: checks to see if a given block is both water and is cold enough to freeze

name: isBlockFreezableNaturally
desc: checks to see if a given block is both water and has at least one immediately adjacent non-water block

name: getBlockPowerInput
desc: Returns the highest redstone signal strength powering the given block. Args: X, Y, Z.

name: isBlockIndirectlyGettingPowered
desc: Used to see if one of the blocks next to you or your block is getting power from a neighboring block. Used by items like TNT or Doors so they don't have redstone going straight into them.  Args: x, y, z

name: isDaytime
desc: Checks whether its daytime by seeing if the light subtracted from the skylight is less than 4

name: getStrongestIndirectPower
desc: Returns the redstone signal the given position is receiving from neighboring blocks.

name: getCurrentMoonPhaseFactor
desc: gets the current fullness of the moon expressed as a float between 1.0 and 0.0, in steps of .25

name: canLightningStrikeAt
desc: Checks to see if there is currently rain hitting this coordinate

name: getDebugLoadedEntities
desc: This string is 'All: (number of loaded entities)' Viewable by press ing F3

name: isBlockHighHumidity
desc: Checks to see if the biome rainfall values for a given x,y,z coordinate set are extremely high

name: getGameRuleStringValue
desc: Gets the GameRule's value as String.

name: setValue
desc: Set this game rule value.

name: getGameRuleBooleanValue
desc: Gets the GameRule's value as boolean.

name: getID
desc: Returns the ID of this game type

name: getByID
desc: Returns the game type with the specified ID, or SURVIVAL if none found. Args: id

name: getByName
desc: Returns the game type with the specified name, or SURVIVAL if none found. This is case sensitive. Args: name

name: configurePlayerCapabilities
desc: Configures the player capabilities based on the game type

name: getName
desc: Returns the name of this game type

name: isAdventure
desc: Returns true if this is the ADVENTURE game type

name: isCreative
desc: Returns true if this is the CREATIVE game type

name: isSurvivalOrAdventure
desc: Returns true if this is the SURVIVAL or ADVENTURE game type

name: removeStalePortalLocations
desc: called periodically to remove out-of-date portal locations from the cache list. Argument par1 is a WorldServer.getTotalWorldTime() value.

name: placeInPortal
desc: Place an entity in a nearby portal, creating one if necessary.

name: placeInExistingPortal
desc: Place an entity in a nearby portal which already exists.

name: getFoliageColorPine
desc: Gets the foliage color for pine type (metadata 1) trees

name: getFoliageColor
desc: Gets foliage color from temperature and humidity. Args: temperature, humidity

name: getFoliageColorBirch
desc: Gets the foliage color for birch type (metadata 2) trees

name: readFromNBT
desc: reads in data from the NBTTagCompound into this MapDataBase

name: setDirty
desc: Sets the dirty state of this MapDataBase, whether it needs saving to disk.

name: writeToNBT
desc: write data to NBTTagCompound from this MapDataBase, similar to Entities and TileEntities

name: markDirty
desc: Marks this MapDataBase dirty, to be saved to disk when the level next saves.

name: isDirty
desc: Whether this MapDataBase needs saving to disk.

name: setCanBeCreated
desc: Sets canBeCreated to the provided value, and returns this.

name: getTranslateName
desc: Gets the translation key for the name of this world type.

name: getTranslatedInfo
desc: Gets the translation key for the info text for this world type.

name: getGeneratorVersion
desc: Returns generatorVersion.

name: getCanBeCreated
desc: Gets whether this WorldType can be used to generate a new world.

name: isVersioned
desc: Returns true if this world Type has a version associated with it.

name: showWorldInfoNotice
desc: returns true if selecting this worldtype from the customize menu should display the generator.[worldtype].info message

name: setVersioned
desc: Flags this world type as having an associated version.

name: setNotificationData
desc: enables the display of generator.[worldtype].info message on the customize world menu

name: getGrassColor
desc: Gets grass color from temperature and humidity. Args: temperature, humidity
